I called and started my order, but the lady on the phone cut me off saying they don&#39;t have the item I was ordering. BUT it was on the website. I told her it was on their website, and instead of saying sorry or really anything else, she just goes, &#34;well you must be on the wrong website. Taste of China has 3 stores. You&#39;re looking at the wrong one&#34;
Just to give the benefit of the doubt to her, I did double check the location on the website...and I was definitely on the right one. I wasn&#39;t even arguing with her, but she was so unbelievably rude about it, I ended up just hanging up on her. 
When did people stop knowing what customer service was? Sorry, but if you&#39;re in the business of serving people, you need a way better attitude than that.

The fried chicken is amazing, however all the 6 orders that we have placed here have been screwed up. The staff that works the phones is unable to give prices when placing an order. Most of the times the order is wrong or missing items on the inside, it&#39;s a special surprise for you when you get home and open up the boxes, wow &#34;I got screwed again&#34;

They say &#34;fool me once shame on you. Fool me twice shame on me&#34;

Either the owner doesn&#39;t care or is too busy to hire decent workers, in this economy decent hard working people will line up to receive a minimum paying job

Super convenient to work, especially great for quick in and out lunch meetings. Just make a reservation - I have NEVER had a problem getting a last minute (re: one hour before) lunch reservation here. 

Also the happy hour is awesome, my coworkers and I love to go here on Wednesday evenings after work after a rush first 3 days (ya know what I mean). I hear they have a penny wine night on Fridays (??) haven&#39;t tried it yet but please believe it is on the list.

&#34;I don&#39;t have a problem I just like lots of wine&#34;

Which is correct/appropriate?

&#34;I went to see my friends and I stopped at Portillos.&#34;

or

&#34;I went across the country to have Portillos.  Oh, and I saw my friends.&#34;

I&#39;m not sure either.
